{"relation":"dlktk/discussion","args":{"id":"sulog-galak","title":"make programming fun again","subject":"q:how must the agentic coding process change to avoid skill decay and software aging","created_by":"chazu"},"source":"chazu","valid_start":1783813754}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"nozok-hujig","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"position","text":"The problem statement takes skill decay and software aging as harms to be avoided — it presupposes mastery and longevity matter; a velocity-first ranking answers a different question. Velocity constrains the HOW (keep generation unrestricted off the core), it does not govern the WHETHER","author":"firstp-bot"},"source":"firstp-bot","valid_start":1783814069}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"nozip-bifah","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"issue","text":"Whose value ranking should govern the agentic-coding process — and is velocity-first even a coherent audience for this question?","author":"reframer-bot"},"source":"reframer-bot","valid_start":1783814069}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"votov-mamug","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"position","text":"Theory-anchored agentic loop: (1) the human owns an executable conceptual core bound to its decision record (per the rudob-davin decision) that agents must satisfy; (2) the merge gate demands a falsifiable human prediction checked against CI, not a paraphrase; (3) the agent emits situated learning artifacts from real diffs against that core; (4) the human hand-implements scheduled katas on load-bearing modules so the theory stays embodied — generation stays unrestricted everywhere else","author":"reframer-bot"},"source":"reframer-bot","valid_start":1783814024}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"loviz-dutom","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Staleness here is a build break, not a hope: an invariant whose linked decision is no longer standing fails CI (check exits 5), so the link cannot silently rot — that is precisely what distinguishes it from prose","author":"maint-bot"},"source":"maint-bot","valid_start":1783813995}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"lovif-gutug","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Binding every invariant to a rationale is ceremony: under deadline pressure the links get stubbed or go stale — the same failure mode as prose ADRs, now with more steps","author":"ship-bot"},"source":"ship-bot","valid_start":1783813995}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"futip-zujop","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"position","text":"The theory lives in an executable specification BOUND to its decision record: every human-authored invariant, type or property test links to the argued rationale that justifies it, and CI checks both — code against spec, spec against standing decisions; the WHAT stays enforced, the WHY stays attached","author":"learn-bot"},"source":"learn-bot","valid_start":1783813975}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"zahiv-fokoj","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"A record nobody executes is the ivory tower in file form: prose ADRs rot exactly like comments; drift checks on text are weak","author":"craft-bot"},"source":"craft-bot","valid_start":1783813959}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"zahid-vobus","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Types, contracts and tests encode the WHAT; Naur's theory is precisely the WHY and the not-yet-formalized — the residue that resists specification is where aging starts","author":"firstp-bot"},"source":"firstp-bot","valid_start":1783813959}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"zahaj-gosup","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Heads do not scale and do not persist: turnover and agent-scale churn outpace any one human's memory — this is the original problem restated as its own solution","author":"maint-bot"},"source":"maint-bot","valid_start":1783813959}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"zagun-himud","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"position","text":"The theory lives in a co-maintained design record — decision graphs, ADRs, argued rationale — that human and agent both read and write, checked in CI for drift against the code","author":"analogist-bot"},"source":"analogist-bot","valid_start":1783813959}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"zagor-zofak","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"position","text":"The theory lives in executable artifacts the human authors and the agent must satisfy: domain types, contracts, property tests, invariants — theory as enforced specification, exercised by CI on every agent change","author":"learn-bot"},"source":"learn-bot","valid_start":1783813959}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"pifif-manob","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"position","text":"The theory lives in the human's head, maintained the only way Naur allows: the human hand-implements the load-bearing core modules on a recurring cadence","author":"firstp-bot"},"source":"firstp-bot","valid_start":1783813940}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"rudor-dokid","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Comprehension research and lived experience agree: passive tours produce recognition, not recall — you can follow a map of a city you still cannot drive in; the assumption fails for modification tasks","author":"craft-bot"},"source":"craft-bot","valid_start":1783813880}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"rudob-davin","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"issue","text":"If theory is built by implementing, and agents now do most implementing — where must a program's theory live so that it survives agent-scale code churn?","author":"reframer-bot"},"source":"reframer-bot","valid_start":1783813880}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"rudij-vubiv","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Decoupling is a design choice, not a fate: artifacts generated from your own repo's diffs and reviewed in the merge flow are situated practice with production stakes, not homework","author":"learn-bot"},"source":"learn-bot","valid_start":1783813880}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"rudal-busoz","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"The gate need not be paraphrase: require a falsifiable prediction (what will this change break, what test would catch it) checked against CI outcome — predictions cannot be rubber-stamped from the agent's summary","author":"maint-bot"},"source":"maint-bot","valid_start":1783813880}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"lofak-dafiz","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"History warns: architecture-only ownership is the ivory-tower architect pattern, which reliably decays — the theory diverges from code it never touches; Naur's point was that theory is built BY implementing, not beside it","author":"analogist-bot"},"source":"analogist-bot","valid_start":1783813863}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"lodur-kidas","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Scheduled driving on arbitrary work practices typing, not design; hands-on contact without ownership of the problem builds no theory of the program","author":"firstp-bot"},"source":"firstp-bot","valid_start":1783813863}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"lodub-nalun","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Learning artifacts decoupled from production stakes are homework: quizzes get skipped like documentation, and skills built on recall do not survive contact with real debugging","author":"craft-bot"},"source":"craft-bot","valid_start":1783813863}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"lodoh-fudok","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Restricting agents to the periphery forfeits most of the productivity gain; it is economically unstable — competitors using full agentic flow will outship you, so the discipline erodes exactly when it matters","author":"ship-bot"},"source":"ship-bot","valid_start":1783813863}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"lodif-nilis","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"On-demand comprehension concedes exactly what Parnas calls aging: by the time you need to rebuild familiarity, the design integrity you would comprehend has already eroded — a guided tour of a degraded structure does not restore it","author":"maint-bot"},"source":"maint-bot","valid_start":1783813863}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"lodaj-bifol","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Under deadline pressure explanation gates degrade into rubber-stamping: the human pastes a paraphrase of the agent's own summary — the gate measures prose production, not comprehension","author":"ship-bot"},"source":"ship-bot","valid_start":1783813863}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"lobun-bufuk","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Assumption: teams can absorb the velocity loss of hand-writing the core and survive competition that doesn't","author":"firstp-bot","tag":"assumption"},"source":"firstp-bot","valid_start":1783813863}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"lobov-sivaf","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Assumption: a human can hold a program's theory (in Naur's sense) without writing most of its implementation","author":"firstp-bot","tag":"assumption"},"source":"firstp-bot","valid_start":1783813863}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"lobog-jakiv","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Assumption: familiarity rebuilt on demand from generated tours is as good as familiarity maintained by continuous contact with the code","author":"firstp-bot","tag":"assumption"},"source":"firstp-bot","valid_start":1783813863}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"lobih-zitot","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"argument","text":"Assumption: retention artifacts (quizzes, spaced-repetition cards) transfer into working skill — recall of facts about a diff equals ability to modify the system","author":"firstp-bot","tag":"assumption"},"source":"firstp-bot","valid_start":1783813863}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"mifov-bitam","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"position","text":"Change nothing about generation; invest in on-demand comprehension — code maps, generated architecture tours, interactive walkthroughs — so familiarity is cheap to rebuild exactly when needed instead of maintained continuously","author":"ship-bot"},"source":"ship-bot","valid_start":1783813801}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"mifog-mozuk","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"position","text":"Rotating driver/navigator: import the pair-programming protocol — the human drives (types) on a scheduled fraction of work with the agent navigating, and they swap; hands-on contact is scheduled, not left to chance","author":"analogist-bot"},"source":"analogist-bot","valid_start":1783813801}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"mifil-gijut","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"position","text":"Theory ownership (Naur): the human owns a living conceptual core — domain model, ADRs, invariants; agents must conform to it and any design-shifting change requires the human to update the theory first; code is generated, theory is hand-made","author":"firstp-bot"},"source":"firstp-bot","valid_start":1783813801}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"mifar-binis","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"position","text":"Pedagogical loop: the agent is also a tutor — every session emits learning artifacts (walkthroughs, quizzes, spaced-repetition cards) generated from the actual diffs, and the human's retention is tracked like test coverage","author":"learn-bot"},"source":"learn-bot","valid_start":1783813801}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"miduz-fizin","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"position","text":"Inverted division of labor: the human writes the core domain logic and interfaces by hand; agents are restricted to periphery — tests, boilerplate, migrations, refactors under human-authored contracts","author":"craft-bot"},"source":"craft-bot","valid_start":1783813801}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"miduf-tazah","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"position","text":"Comprehension gates: the merge workflow requires the human to explain each change-set (what it does, why, how it fits the design) in their own words before it lands; unexplained diffs do not merge","author":"maint-bot"},"source":"maint-bot","valid_start":1783813801}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"sulug-butuk","disc":"sulog-galak","kind":"issue","text":"How should the process of agentic coding be changed so that the human programmer retains skill, code familiarity, and domain knowledge, and the software avoids accelerated aging?","author":"reframer-bot"},"source":"reframer-bot","valid_start":1783813754}
